### Loading
- `.env` is loaded in settings via `python-dotenv`: see [`news_trader/settings.py`](mdc:news_trader/settings.py)

### Important variables
- Django: `SECRET_KEY`, `DEBUG`, `ALLOWED_HOSTS`, `DATABASE_URL`
- Celery/Redis: `CELERY_BROKER_URL`, `CELERY_RESULT_BACKEND`
- OpenAI: `OPENAI_API_KEY`
- Alpaca: `ALPACA_API_KEY`, `ALPACA_SECRET_KEY`, `ALPACA_BASE_URL`
- News APIs: `NEWSAPI_KEY`, `ALPHAVANTAGE_API_KEY`, `REDDIT_USER_AGENT`
- Scraping flags: `ENABLE_SELENIUM_SCRAPING` (default true), `SCRAPE_RECENT_HOURS`
- Headless Chrome (Docker): `CHROME_BIN`, `CHROME_PATH`, `DISPLAY`

### Notes
- DRF defaults to `IsAuthenticated` in production settings
- Tests override auth to include tokens per [`news_trader/test_settings.py`](mdc:news_trader/test_settings.py)
- Never commit real keys; keep `.env` local or use secret managers in production